<p>I need to convert a JS date object to a php Y-m-d string using javascript as this value will be inserted in a mysql datetime data type. The code below does the trick but it's messy, any alternatives?</p>  <pre><code>var jsDateObj = new Date, phpYear = jsDateObj.getFullYear(), phpMonth = jsDateObj.getMonth() + 1, phpDate = jsDateObj.getDate(), phpDate = phpYear + "-" + (10 &gt; phpMonth ? "0" + phpMonth : phpMonth) + "-" + (10 &gt; phpDate ? "0" + phpDate : phpDate); console.log(phpDate); // 2015-10-02 </code></pre>